I got a couple of guys.

00:03:54.753 --> 00:03:55.655
We'll take it from there."

00:03:56.175 --> 00:03:59.318
And then, the whole story in Numbers

00:03:59.377 --> 00:04:02.000
fifteen with those the three animals,

00:04:02.401 --> 00:04:06.343
the ram, the bull and the goat,

00:04:06.844 --> 00:04:10.288
resolving every problem of his people and

00:04:10.548 --> 00:04:13.090
rectifying their relationship and how they

00:04:13.110 --> 00:04:14.912
would all work together in the end to

00:04:15.491 --> 00:04:16.492
accomplish this.

00:04:16.874 --> 00:04:17.733
And it just goes on.

00:04:17.793 --> 00:04:19.276
And then you have in Dabarym

00:04:19.315 --> 00:04:21.076
that powerful announcement about

00:04:22.519 --> 00:04:25.360
the Nakary making a debut right

00:04:25.380 --> 00:04:28.702
there, and the Towrah, I'm just so happy,

00:04:28.723 --> 00:04:31.345
Qara, that you've decided to join

00:04:31.404 --> 00:04:33.146
us in this way. That's very cute of

00:04:33.206 --> 00:04:36.009
you to do so, and so I

00:04:36.028 --> 00:04:37.370
was just minding my own business I

00:04:37.389 --> 00:04:40.091
was making my way through just one

00:04:40.312 --> 00:04:43.053
after another and Leah comes into my

00:04:43.115 --> 00:04:45.976
study before sunrise, before sunrise one

00:04:46.016 --> 00:04:46.237
morning

00:04:47.230 --> 00:04:48.550
And she says," right now,

00:04:48.850 --> 00:04:52.911
you need to read the final Mashal,

00:04:53.012 --> 00:04:54.692
number thirty-one, with me.

00:04:55.413 --> 00:04:56.432
And we read through this.

00:04:56.612 --> 00:04:58.233
And I don't know if we would have

00:04:58.254 --> 00:05:01.235
had the eyes to see it if we

00:05:01.254 --> 00:05:03.035
had come across it a year ago or

00:05:03.074 --> 00:05:05.495
two years ago or much any earlier.

00:05:05.576 --> 00:05:06.776
We would just not have had the eyes

00:05:06.797 --> 00:05:09.298
to see it.

00:05:09.358 --> 00:05:14.098
And it is Dowd who was saying that

00:05:14.139 --> 00:05:15.759
he was visited by a surrogate mother,

00:05:17.569 --> 00:05:20.490
and that she imparted information to him

00:05:21.129 --> 00:05:22.110
that was life-altering.

00:05:23.810 --> 00:05:28.552
And then that mother is identified,

00:05:29.271 --> 00:05:32.473
and her husband is identified,

00:05:33.613 --> 00:05:37.095
and it becomes us.

00:05:37.194 --> 00:05:37.834
We are looking at...

00:05:39.206 --> 00:05:41.208
I had to spend three days saying that

00:05:41.228 --> 00:05:41.908
that's not possible.

00:05:41.928 --> 00:05:42.889
You can't go back in time.

00:05:42.949 --> 00:05:43.509
Here we are.

00:05:44.370 --> 00:05:45.271
It didn't make sense at first.

00:05:45.290 --> 00:05:47.492
You cannot go back in time and alter

00:05:47.572 --> 00:05:47.951
anything.

00:05:47.971 --> 00:05:50.194
You can witness what happened in the past.

00:05:50.374 --> 00:05:51.074
That's it.

00:05:51.113 --> 00:05:53.315
Because that's the way that light works;

00:05:53.815 --> 00:05:54.336
light energy.

00:05:54.596 --> 00:05:56.937
But, you can't alter anything in the past,

00:05:57.458 --> 00:05:59.639
and this is life altering.

00:05:59.658 --> 00:06:03.182
She tried to talk some sense into the

00:06:03.201 --> 00:06:04.721
young man and get him to think about

00:06:04.762 --> 00:06:05.223
who he was.

00:06:06.637 --> 00:06:08.100
I went back through the Mashal,

00:06:08.120 --> 00:06:10.262
and I got up to sixteen,

00:06:10.322 --> 00:06:12.184
and it's still the same discussion.

00:06:13.345 --> 00:06:14.004
Yeah,

00:06:14.185 --> 00:06:16.408
the Mashal are all written from the

00:06:16.447 --> 00:06:19.630
perspective of a husband and wife,

00:06:19.891 --> 00:06:22.153
a mother and father,

00:06:22.774 --> 00:06:24.875
providing advice to their son,

00:06:25.896 --> 00:06:28.238
all in harmony with the Yahowah's Towrah

00:06:28.259 --> 00:06:28.740
instructions.

00:06:30.305 --> 00:06:32.906
It's the same all the way through these

00:06:33.007 --> 00:06:33.507
Mashal.

00:06:33.567 --> 00:06:36.249
And they're beautiful family portraits,

00:06:37.249 --> 00:06:38.170
if you will.

00:06:38.290 --> 00:06:40.031
And so, you can say they were written

00:06:40.071 --> 00:06:40.571
by Dowd,

00:06:40.651 --> 00:06:41.872
and I think most of them were,

00:06:41.911 --> 00:06:43.932
but they could have also been written by

00:06:43.992 --> 00:06:45.334
Solomon in his early years,

00:06:45.733 --> 00:06:46.574
him trying to...

00:06:48.857 --> 00:06:50.718
share what he had learned from his father,

00:06:50.738 --> 00:06:51.639
the problem of, of course,

00:06:51.720 --> 00:06:53.401
ascribing them to Solomon.

00:06:53.442 --> 00:06:55.524
His mother was a tramp,

00:06:55.564 --> 00:06:57.245
and by the time that he was born,

00:06:57.286 --> 00:07:02.951
his father was a drunk and was a

00:07:02.992 --> 00:07:04.793
lousy father, a lousy husband,

00:07:05.795 --> 00:07:06.636
a lousy leader,

00:07:06.836 --> 00:07:08.538
lousy everything by the time that he was

00:07:08.658 --> 00:07:08.757
born.

00:07:08.778 --> 00:07:11.261
The metaphors he uses to describe

00:07:12.451 --> 00:07:16.192
The parents suggest a poor upbringing.

00:07:17.394 --> 00:07:17.494
Yeah.

00:07:17.533 --> 00:07:22.136
So, it suggests that everything we read

00:07:22.156 --> 00:07:23.776
from Dowd, actually,

00:07:23.836 --> 00:07:25.896
because of this intervention of...

00:07:26.297 --> 00:07:31.478
Dowd didn't... Listen, what...

00:07:31.538 --> 00:07:32.459
Back one step further.

00:07:33.660 --> 00:07:38.422
My life over the last ten to twelve

00:07:38.482 --> 00:07:38.762
years...

00:07:40.057 --> 00:07:41.898
of the twenty-four years that I have done

00:07:41.918 --> 00:07:45.059
this, since I've met you,

00:07:45.079 --> 00:07:48.079
has been devoted to burnishing Dowd's

00:07:48.120 --> 00:07:48.579
resume.

00:07:50.259 --> 00:07:51.521
I think all of you have been with

00:07:51.560 --> 00:07:52.821
me, in fact, I know you have,

00:07:53.060 --> 00:07:55.982
long enough to know when everyone started

00:07:56.021 --> 00:07:57.742
to mock me because I had a bromance

00:07:57.783 --> 00:07:58.043
with Dowd.

00:07:58.062 --> 00:08:01.444
And, that grew from recognizing that he was

00:08:01.504 --> 00:08:02.963
also the Messiah and Son of God.

00:08:03.605 --> 00:08:04.264
And then, that grew,

00:08:04.689 --> 00:08:06.350
which is a marvelous thing.

00:08:06.370 --> 00:08:06.850
Yeah,

00:08:06.870 --> 00:08:09.771
and then that grew when I recognized that

00:08:10.050 --> 00:08:13.132
he was the exemplar.

00:08:13.732 --> 00:08:15.452
He was the epitome of what God was

00:08:15.492 --> 00:08:16.892
trying to achieve through the covenant,

00:08:16.932 --> 00:08:19.733
and that he also represented Yisra'el,

00:08:19.894 --> 00:08:21.894
the good, the bad, the beautiful,

00:08:21.934 --> 00:08:22.413
and the ugly,

00:08:22.853 --> 00:08:25.694
and that the next phase of that was

00:08:25.935 --> 00:08:27.194
the greatest discovery, I think,

00:08:27.235 --> 00:08:29.016
in human history is to recognize that it

00:08:29.036 --> 00:08:30.055
was God who fulfilled

00:08:31.067 --> 00:08:31.749
Pesach, Matsah,

00:08:31.769 --> 00:08:33.028
and Bikuwrym being crucified in

00:08:33.068 --> 00:08:33.929
33 CE,

00:08:33.970 --> 00:08:36.071
and then taking our guilt into She’owl on

00:08:36.110 --> 00:08:36.510
Matsah,

00:08:37.051 --> 00:08:39.232
and that he wrote about it in first-person

00:08:39.273 --> 00:08:39.793
narratives,

00:08:40.273 --> 00:08:41.754
and therefore there could not have been a

00:08:41.813 --> 00:08:42.193
Jesus,

00:08:42.234 --> 00:08:43.855
because Dowd actually did these things,

00:08:43.955 --> 00:08:45.535
and the Jesus figure is simply a

00:08:45.615 --> 00:08:46.076
counterfeit.

00:08:46.096 --> 00:08:49.177
You know,

00:08:49.197 --> 00:08:51.158
that was probably four years ago,

00:08:51.278 --> 00:08:52.059
five years ago,

00:08:52.100 --> 00:08:53.980
that we came to that conclusion and was

00:08:54.020 --> 00:08:54.620
able to prove it.

00:08:56.660 --> 00:08:57.481
And ever since then,

00:08:57.802 --> 00:09:00.423
my life has been pretty much devoted to

00:09:01.784 --> 00:09:04.047
reestablishing Dowd's reputation that was

00:09:04.147 --> 00:09:05.988
stolen from him by Judaism and

00:09:06.028 --> 00:09:08.870
Christianity, and to some extent, Islam.

00:09:10.591 --> 00:09:11.993
But there was always this nagging

00:09:13.634 --> 00:09:16.735
heartache.

00:09:16.775 --> 00:09:16.975
Well,

00:09:18.096 --> 00:09:20.558
we love and respect our king because he

00:09:20.599 --> 00:09:22.740
fulfilled the single most difficult

00:09:22.780 --> 00:09:24.322
challenge in human history.

00:09:25.298 --> 00:09:26.779
I mean, allowing the Romans,

00:09:26.980 --> 00:09:29.662
volunteering to let the Romans crucify

00:09:29.682 --> 00:09:29.822
you,

00:09:30.883 --> 00:09:33.465
and then having your soul go into hell,

00:09:33.524 --> 00:09:35.787
shield, carry our guilt away on its own.

00:09:35.886 --> 00:09:39.369
That's the greatest act of courage in

00:09:39.408 --> 00:09:39.950
human history.

00:09:40.669 --> 00:09:42.711
And we're here because he did that.

00:09:43.131 --> 00:09:43.832
If he hadn't done that,

00:09:43.873 --> 00:09:44.653
we wouldn't even be here.

00:09:45.874 --> 00:09:49.356
And so we have been devoted, but...

00:09:50.884 --> 00:09:53.767
Those who are the least bit scholarly on

00:09:53.787 --> 00:09:55.628
this, all rabbis,

00:09:56.889 --> 00:09:59.291
and many Christian advocates,

00:10:00.532 --> 00:10:02.673
will push back on the idea that Dowd

00:10:02.714 --> 00:10:06.456
could have been the Messiah who is also

00:10:06.535 --> 00:10:11.139
our Savior because of what Dowd did to

00:10:11.639 --> 00:10:13.302
Uriah, the light of Yah,

00:10:14.523 --> 00:10:16.644
when stealing his wife.

00:10:16.803 --> 00:10:17.404
Mm-hmm.

00:10:18.311 --> 00:10:19.931
And they will, in fact,

00:10:19.971 --> 00:10:21.312
we've had them post on our site.

00:10:21.591 --> 00:10:24.611
You cannot be right because the Passover

00:10:24.631 --> 00:10:25.773
lamb has to be perfect.

00:10:26.332 --> 00:10:27.913
And Dowd did the following.

00:10:27.952 --> 00:10:34.815
David did the following to Uriah's wife

00:10:34.894 --> 00:10:35.914
and then had him killed.

00:10:37.674 --> 00:10:40.615
And yeah, that absolutely happens.

00:10:40.676 --> 00:10:41.975
And they'll say the Passover lamb has to

00:10:41.995 --> 00:10:42.436
be perfect.

00:10:43.317 --> 00:10:44.716
Yeah, well, Moshe killed a man.

00:10:45.309 --> 00:10:46.831
Yeah, so, yeah, well, he did.

00:10:46.892 --> 00:10:48.832
Yeah, that's right.

00:10:49.514 --> 00:10:51.174
But they don't relate.

00:10:51.956 --> 00:10:54.138
And so you have two issues here.

00:10:56.299 --> 00:11:02.846
The first is we have never addressed what

00:11:02.865 --> 00:11:03.086
Dowd did.

00:11:03.105 --> 00:11:04.648
You know,

00:11:04.668 --> 00:11:06.529
we've been all through Second Samuel,

00:11:06.549 --> 00:11:10.653
but never Eleven and Twelve that addressed

00:11:10.692 --> 00:11:11.094
what Dowd did.

00:11:13.230 --> 00:11:16.114
And finally, after this review in Isaiah,

00:11:16.153 --> 00:11:17.836
Isaiah, Isaiah, Isaiah, Isaiah, Isaiah,

00:11:17.855 --> 00:11:18.615
Isaiah, Isaiah, Isaiah, Isaiah, Isaiah,

00:11:18.635 --> 00:11:19.356
Isaiah, Isaiah, Isaiah, Isaiah, Isaiah,

00:11:19.376 --> 00:11:20.857
Isaiah, Isaiah, Isaiah, Isaiah, Isaiah,

00:11:20.899 --> 00:11:21.818
Isaiah, Isaiah, Isaiah, Isaiah, Isaiah,

00:11:21.839 --> 00:11:25.243
Isaiah, Isaiah, Isaiah, Isaiah, Isaiah,

00:11:26.433 --> 00:11:28.034
And it was the most painful thing I

00:11:28.294 --> 00:11:29.054
think I've ever done,

00:11:29.316 --> 00:11:32.397
translating what he did and how he went

00:11:32.417 --> 00:11:32.756
